<HEADLINE>
<P>
E. C. DOTHARD; GEORGIA TROOPER GRAZED BY BULLET MEANT FOR WALLACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
E. C. Dothard, 58, a state trooper grazed in the abdomen by a gunshot in the 
1972 assassination attempt on Alabama Gov. George C. Wallace. Capt. Dothard, 
who served 5 1/2 years as state public safety director and was Wallace's chief 
security guard during the governor's presidential campaign, shot himself Dec. 
15 in a hospital in Anniston, Ala., where he had been found to have a terminal 
malignancy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
