<HEADLINE>
<P>
SADIE L. ORNITZ; WIFE OF BLACKLISTED SCREENWRITER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sadie L. Ornitz, 99, widow of Samuel Ornitz, a screenwriter who was one of the 
Hollywood 10 imprisoned for his political views during the McCarthy era. In 
1987 she was featured prominently in the public television documentary "Legacy 
of the Hollywood Blacklist." Mrs. Ornitz, a suffragette in her youth, also was 
president of the Hollywood Women's Council, a peace activist group which began 
at the time of the Spanish Civil War in the 1930s. At the Motion Picture 
Country Home and Hospital in Woodland Hills on Dec. 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
