<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: STUDY GROUP BACKS NEW LIGHT RAIL LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An organization of local government officials and businesses recommended Friday 
that a light rail line be built linking Los Angeles' Mid-Wilshire area to 
Southwest Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Construction of the rail line would ease traffic congestion along the Crenshaw 
Boulevard corridor and provide a mass transit alternative to an area that is 
expected to see thousands of new jobs in the coming years, the Southern 
California Assn. of Governments said in its study. The cost of building the 
line and its exact route were not addressed by the group. 
</P>
<P>
The study researched the current and future transportation needs of the 
39-square-mile area, bounded by the Santa Monica Freeway to the north, the 
Harbor Freeway to the east, Imperial Highway to the south and the San Diego 
Freeway to the west. 
</P>
</TEXT>
