<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOROTHY DOSTAL DIES; FOUNDED SCHOOL FOR HEARING IMPAIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dorothy Dostal, wife of former Newport Beach Mayor Milan Dostal, died at Hoag 
Hospital on Thursday after a 10-month bout with cancer. 
</P>
<P>
She was born Dorothy Agnes Olson on May 4, 1929, and married Dostal in 1951 in 
Hutchinson, Minn. She was active for several years in the National Charity 
League and with the local Philharmonic Assn. 
</P>
<P>
She was ordained an elder of St. Andrew's Presbyterian Church of Newport Beach 
and was active on the music and the adult education committees. However, she 
was best known for founding Oralingua School for the Hearing Impaired in 
Whittier. 
</P>
<P>
She is survived by her husband and three children: Richard George, 32; Cynthia 
Marie, 29, and Pamela Ann, 24. 
</P>
<P>
A public viewing will be held at Pacific View Mortuary, 3500 Pacific View 
Drive, on Sunday from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The funeral will be at St. Andrew's Presbyterian Church, 600 St. Andrews Road, 
Newport Beach, on Tuesday at 11 a.m. 
</P>
