<HEADLINE>
<P>
TELEVISION COULD HAVE CLEARED THE GRAY AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The officials did not have the advantage that Chick Hearn, Stu Lantz and the 
television audience had: We saw the Laker brawl from three different angles, 
replayed about a half-dozen times. The officials' call of the fight was totally 
out of line. Stuart Gray went on a one-man rampage and should have been the 
only player ejected. 
</P>
<P>
In this case, the officials would have made a much better call if they had 
viewed the television coverage. Granted, basketball is probably much too 
fast-moving for TV replays to settle most questionable calls; but in a drastic 
case, such as Gray's outburst, the officials need the eyes of TV cameras. 
</P>
<P>
KATHIE TARBELL, Huntington Beach 
</P>
