<HEADLINE>
<P>
HERE'S A FUND WAY TO SUPPLEMENT NFL DRAFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the issue of NFL teams drafting underclassmen and the potential 
damage to marginal players, how is this for a solution: 
</P>
<P>
Any NFL team signing a player with eligibility remaining should be required to 
fund a $100,000 trust fund for the player. Such fund could be used only for the 
athlete's continuing college education. 
</P>
<P>
The effect is to protect the athlete's opportunity to get a college education 
and also to raise the stakes for teams that draft underclassmen. 
</P>
<P>
JEFF YOUNG, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
