<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNSPORTSMANLIKE WRITING GETS LITERARY CRITIQUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the life of me, I cannot understand why Jim Murray would compare the 
Houston Oilers to the defendants at Nuremberg. 
</P>
<P>
Murray, referring to Cincinnati's drubbing of the Oilers, states, "We haven't 
seen this kind of runaway kicking of a man when he was down since Nuremberg." 
</P>
<P>
Now, I can sympathize with a proud group of athletes that is humiliated. But 
the defendants at Nuremberg? 
</P>
<P>
Many people fear that the horror of the Holocaust will begin to fade in time. 
It is grossly insensitive statements like Murray's that hurry the process 
along. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL ALLEN, Mission Hills 
</P>
