<HEADLINE>
<P>
MILLER NAMED MOST VALUABLE BY CHARGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON PATTERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wide receiver Anthony Miller has been chosen by his teammates as the Chargers' 
most valuable player this season. 
</P>
<P>
Other Charger awards were given to outside linebacker Ken Woodard (best special 
teams player), defensive ends Leslie O'Neal and Lee Williams (best linemen) and 
cornerback Gill Byrd (most inspirational). 
</P>
<P>
Miller, in his second year out of Tennessee, has caught 70 passes for 1,199 
yards and 10 touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
Woodard leads the special teams with 12 tackles. He deflected a punt to set up 
the winning touchdown Nov. 12 against the Raiders. 
</P>
<P>
O'Neal is second in total tackles with 88. Williams is fourth with 66 and was 
selected to the Pro Bowl this week for the second consecutive season. 
</P>
<P>
Byrd has seven interceptions, tops for AFC cornerbacks. He has 25 career 
interceptions, which ties him for second on the team's all-time list with Kenny 
Graham. DON PATTERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Receiver Anthony Miller scored 10 touchdowns for the Chargers. DAVE 
GATLEY / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
