<P>
ART FROM EUROPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re "ART/LA89 Draws Mixed Reviews From Local, Out-of-Town Dealers" by Suzanne 
Muchnic, Dec. 12: 
</P>
<P>
I was amused by the Europeans' dismay regarding local collectors' lack of 
sufficient interest in European art -- as if we should roll over and play dead 
for anything from Europe. 
</P>
<P>
The fact is that most of what came over from across the Atlantic was just not 
that good or new, in the opinion of many attending ART/LA89. Just because 
something is esoteric and ugly does not mean that it should automatically 
qualify as art. 
</P>
<P>
Could it be that local collectors don't care for the hodgepodge of detritus 
that European galleries try to push off on what they think is an uneducated 
local public? Convincing us of the merit of the work that they represent should 
be more than hanging it and then criticizing us for not salivating at its very 
sight. 
</P>
<P>
S. RICHARD HURWITZ 
</P>
<P>
Blue Jay, Calif. 
</P>
