<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE SEEK GUNMAN IN SANTA SUIT WHO KILLED 1 MAN, WOUNDED 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From A Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bakersfield police continued to search Friday for a gunman wearing a Santa 
Claus suit who, for no apparent reason, shot one man to death and wounded 
another in the parking lot of a coffee shop. 
</P>
<P>
Kenneth Obney, 36, of Joshua Tree died of multiple gunshots and a companion 
suffered an arm wound in the attack Thursday evening outside a Denny's 
restaurant, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The wounded man, who was reported in fair condition at a local hospital, was 
not identified. 
</P>
<P>
The victims were walking toward their pickup truck after making a phone call to 
arrange the sale of German shepherd puppies that were in the vehicle when the 
assailant in the Santa outfit suddenly appeared, pulled a rifle from a 
gift-wrapped package and opened fire, police said. 
</P>
<P>
After the shooting, the assailant quickly disappeared into heavy fog that had 
fallen over the area, police said. 
</P>
<P>
A witness said authorities took two puppies from a camper shell on the pickup 
and took them to an animal shelter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FUGITIVES; MURDERS -- CALIFORNIA; SHOOTINGS -- CALIFORNIA; IMPOSTERS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122389-0079 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 152662 </DOCID>
<DATE>
