<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNTY PANEL MOVES TO SETTLE EMBEZZLEMENT 
SUIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a move that is expected to settle a lawsuit against an accountant who 
pleaded no contest to embezzling more than $530,000 in county Fire Department 
funds, the Los Angeles County Claims Board Friday recommended accepting his 
wife's portion of their property. 
</P>
<P>
Last month, the Board of Supervisors proposed the settlement of its lawsuit 
against William Paternostro, 41, who was suspected of taking more than $800,000 
from a department account he controlled. Under the terms of the agreement, 
Paternostro will hand over his 4,462-square-foot Mt. Washington home, valued at 
more than $600,000, and other assets he allegedly accumulated while embezzling 
the money. 
</P>
<P>
Because the suit was also filed against the accountant's estranged wife, 
Margaret, she offered to deed her portion of their home and other shared 
property to settle the matter, claims officials said. 
</P>
