</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
72 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Feb. 13 trial was set during an arraignment in Stockton, Calif., for Mike 
Blatt, former Seattle Seahawk general manager who is charged with the murder of 
a former business partner. 
</P>
<P>
Blatt, 44, is accused of hiring the murder of Lawrence Carnegie. Carnegie, a 
real estate broker, was slain last Feb. 28 by an arrow shot from a crossbow 
after being lured to an empty home by a caller who said he was considering 
buying the house. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
MURDERS -- CALIFORNIA; BLATT, MICHAEL; MURDER FOR HIRE 
