<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAKERS PUT MCCANTS ON INJURED LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SAM McMANIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mel McCants, the Lakers' rookie forward who has been bothered for the last 
three weeks by sprains in both ankles, was put on the injured list Friday. 
</P>
<P>
McCants, who sprained his right ankle on Nov. 24 and his left ankle a few days 
later, will miss a minimum of five games. The 6-foot-9, 250-pound free agent 
from Purdue, has played in only four games for the Lakers, his last appearance 
coming Nov. 17 against Denver. 
</P>
<P>
The Lakers did not say whether they will replace McCants on the roster. He is 
eligible to be reactivated on Jan. 9, when the Lakers play at Phoenix. SAM 
McMANIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
