<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DIGGERS, PLANTERS : GARDENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
* To keep weeds in check during the winter rains and give a neat appearance to 
your flower beds, weed now and apply a layer of mulch. 
</P>
<P>
* If you have hard-packed soil, including clay, be sure to apply gypsum or 
other additives to the yard in order to break the barriers to water 
penetration. 
</P>
<P>
* Did you spray your peaches and nectarines to prevent peach leaf curl yet? If 
not, do so immediately and then follow it up with another spraying before the 
buds swell. 
</P>
<P>
* Leave your poinsettias in the pot after the blossoms have gone and put them 
outside in a protected area, watering them occasionally. Plant them in the 
ground only after all chance of frost is gone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
