<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Laguna Art Museum has received a challenge grant from the Kathryn G. 
Thompson Development Co. of Irvine to match, dollar-for dollar, each new or 
upgraded membership received during the museum's winter, 1990, membership 
campaign. The grant, of up to $30,000, will double the value of members' 
contributions, thus giving them the benefits of a higher membership level. 
</P>
<P>
The Newport Harbor Art Museum will give a progress report in early 1990 on the 
campaign to raise $50 million for its new building, due to open in 1993, 
President Thomas H. Nielsen said this week. So far, the museum has raised $10 
million, officials report. Progress in the search for a new director -- former 
director Kevin E. Consey resigned in August -- and design details for the new 
museum building also will also be announced, Nielsen said. 
</P>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
